85 (5) Allowances and funding.
86 (A) The legislative members of the commission shall receive the allowances provided
87 for in Code Section 28-1-8 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated. The allowances
88 authorized by this resolution shall not be received by any member of the commission
89 for more than 15 days unless additional days are authorized. Funds necessary to carry
90 out the provisions of this resolution shall come from funds appropriated to the Senate
91 and the House of Representatives.
92 (B) In order to effectively carry out its duties and responsibilities, such commission
93 may employ consultants and contract with persons, firms, or corporations to provide
94 research and other assistance as the commission deems proper and necessary; provided,
95 however, that the amount of any funds proposed to be spent for such services shall first
96 be approved, in writing, by the Speaker of the House of Representatives and President
97 of the Senate.
98 (6) Report.
99 (A) The commission shall issue a report of its findings and work and shall report the
100 resolution of any boundary line questions or recommendations. The chairpersons shall
101 file a report of the same prior to the date of abolishment specified in this resolution,
102 subject to subparagraph (C) of this paragraph.
103 (B) In the event the commission adopts a report that does not include suggestions for
104 proposed legislation, the cochairpersons shall file the report, subject to
105 subparagraph (C) of this paragraph.
106 (C) No report shall be filed unless the same has been approved prior to the date of
107 abolishment specified in this resolution by majority vote of a quorum of the
108 commission. A report so approved shall be signed by the cochairperson of the
109 commission and filed with the Secretary of the Senate and the Clerk of the House of
110 Representatives.
